HTML -> Hyper Text Markup Language
- Not programming Language
- Markup Language
- Browser Doesnot display html tags
- Elements are building block
- Describe structure of Web Page


WHY HTML ?
- To create website
- Can Become Web designer or Web developer
- Understand the web
- Can make responsible and real-world websites


HTML VS HTML 5 (HTML 5 is lastes version)


Basic HTML Document
    <!DOCTYPE html> // Defines HTML 5 document
    <html> // html opening tag -> Root tag
        <head> // html Header
            <title>This is document title</title> // Display in browser title
        </head>

        <body>
            <h1>My first heading</h1>
            <p>My first paragraph</p>
        </body>
    </html>


HTML element Syntax
<tagame>Content Goes Here</tagame>

Important KEY points
- Must start with <!Document html>
- Begins with <html> and ends with <!html> 
- Visible part -> <body> and </body>
- Never skip the end tag or closing tag
- .html extension

Requirements : 
-- Web Browser -> Firefox , Opera mini, Internet Explorer, Safari, Chrome Browser
-- Code Editor -> Notepad++, Visual Studio code editor, Atom, Sublime Text 3, Brackets code editor

HEADING : 
- Title or Subtitle
- Bold and block elements
- Different sizes
- H1 is most important heading
- H6 is least important heading
- 6 different levels of heading --> <h1> , <h2>, <h3>, <h4>, <h5>, <h6> 

PARAGRAPH : 
- Starts on a new line
- Block element
- <p> element
- Add some whitespace
- Remove any extra spaces
- Always use with heading

PRE : 
- preformatted text
- Display as it is
- Presevers spaces and line breaks

BLOCK Elements : 
- Default display value 
- Block element always starts with new line
- Block element --> <blockquote>, <div>, <form>, <h1> - <h6>, <hr>, <li>, <nav>, <ol>, <pre>, <p>, <table>, <ul>, <video>

INLINE Elements : 
- Does not start with new line
- Inline element --> <a>, <b>, <big>, <br>, <button>, <em>, <i>, <img>, <input>, <label>, <small>, <span>, <strong>, <sup>, <sub>, <textarea>, <select>

DIV :
- used as a container 
- No required attributes
- Together with CSS
- Devision or section 
- Container
- Easily styled
- Place a line brake
- Any Content

SPAN : 
- Inline container
- No required attributes
- Together with CSS
- Easily styled

HTML Horizontal Rules : 
- defines a thematic break
- Separate content
- Separate
- <hr> generates horizontal line
- Enpty tag
- No end tag / closing tag

HTML line breaks : 
- <br> -> Defines line break
- Empty tag

HTML Comment : 
- Not displayed in browser
- Great for debugging
- Hide old content

HTML Images : 
- <img> element
- Linked to web pages
- Empty tag
- Support mltiple image types
- Inline element
Attributes --> 
    - src, alt, widht and height

HTML Links : 
- <a> Tag
- Link text & Images
Attributes --> 
    - href, title, download
    - target -> _blank, _self


HTML Table : 
- Arrange data into rows and columns 
- Arrange Data
- <table> ... </table> Tag 
- <tr> -> Table Row
        - Contains <th> & <td>
- <th> -> Table Head
        - Bold and centered 
        - Header Information 
- <td> -> Table Data
        - Data containers 
        - Regular and left-aligned 
        - contain all sorts of HTML elements


